<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870921-0043 </DOCNO><HL> McDonnell Receives$361.8 Million of JobsFrom U.S. Military</HL><DD> 09/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MD ARC BA ALD SMF GE TXT WX GMAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Units of McDonnell Douglas Corp. received contracts totaling $361.8 million for FA-18 aircraft production for the Navy, aircraft equipment parts for the Air Force and helicopter improvements for the Army.    Atlantic Richfield Co.'s Arco Petroleum Products Co. was awarded a $273.5 million contract from the Defense Logistics Agency for jet fuel and diesel fuel.    Boeing Co. won a $39.5 million Air Force contract for aircraft equipment.    Allied-Signal Inc. got an $18.7 million Air Force contract for aircraft-engine fuel controls.    Units of Singer Co. received contracts totaling $16.5 million to develop communications terminals for the Air Force and electronic equipment for the Navy.    Units of General Electric Co. got contracts totaling $16.1 million for aircraft engine parts for the Air Force and Navy.    Bell Helicopter Textron, a unit of Textron Inc., was issued a $15 million Navy contract to produce AH-1W helicopters.    Westinghouse Electric Corp. units got contracts totaling $12.9 million for antenna parts for the Air Force and support for mine-sweeping systems for the Navy.    AAI Engineering Support Inc. received Air Force contracts totaling $12.7 million for maintenance of training equipment.    Units of General Motors Corp. received contracts totaling $11.6 million for bomb-targeting equipment support for the Navy and electronics research and helicopter engines for the Army. </TEXT></DOC>